caption.p: Maximum strains recorded as a fraction of the breaking strain for the individual web components for the various climatic conditions are as follows: low temperature (+1% max strain, +18% mean stiffness) ( A), medium temperature ( B) and high temperature (−1% max strain, −18% mean stiffness) ( C) and low humidity (−78% max strain, +94% mean stiffness) ( D), medium humidity ( E) and high humidity (+78% max strain, −94% mean stiffness) ( F).
